DESCRIPTION=" Epoxy is a library for handling OpenGL function pointer management by hiding the complexity of dlopen(), dlsym(), glXGetProcAddress(), ... from the developer. Features: * Automatically initializes as new GL functions are used. * GL 4.4 core and compatibility context support. * GLES 1/2/3 context support. * Knows about function aliases so (e.g.) glBufferData() can be used with GL_ARB_vertex_buffer_object implementations, along with GL 1.5+ implementations. * EGL, GLX, and WGL support. * Can be mixed with non-epoxy GL usage."
